Ask HN: What was the website which compiled a person's all media appearences?
text:
Was submitted to HN around two years ago, potentially a 'Show HN' post. This website catalogued at least interviews a person has appeared in, podcast appearances, articles written by and tweets (likely scraped from their profile; I block the Twitter domains at the DNS level). At least +200 votes, quite certainly.

From what I recall, seemingly was mostly focused on people working on various fields of science and research. I (only) remember that John Carmack (the co-founder of id Software, later at Oculus VR) had a page there.

I had the website bookmarked, but when accessing not-so-long-time after the HN submission all links appeared to be redirecting to the frontpage and I got the impression that their project had morphed into something else entirely or was in the process of winding down. But I may very well have been mistaken.

Show HN: Responsible API – OpenAPI toolkit for building robust HTTP APIs
text:
OpenAPI is a maintenance nightmare, but has tons of tooling around it.

Responsible is a small language that compiles to OpenAPI for better maintainability.

And it comes with some testing practices
